# ── Layered Voice Agents example ─────────────────────────────────────────────
# The two agents (front / worker) run server-side and talk to a model provider
# through glove-core's createAdapter.
#
# Default provider is OpenRouter, using affordable open models. Set your key:
OPENROUTER_API_KEY=sk-or-...

# ── Optional overrides ───────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Provider for both agents. Default: openrouter.
# VOICE_PROVIDER=openrouter

# Default open models on OpenRouter:
#   front  = openai/gpt-oss-120b   (spoken persona; its <speech> spans stream into TTS)
#   worker = minimax/minimax-m2.5  (heavy lifting + a ton of tool calls over the DB)
# Override any role independently:
# FRONT_MODEL=openai/gpt-oss-120b
# WORKER_MODEL=minimax/minimax-m2.5

# To use Anthropic instead:
#   VOICE_PROVIDER=anthropic
#   ANTHROPIC_API_KEY=sk-ant-...
# (defaults to claude-haiku-4-5 for front and claude-sonnet-4 for worker)

# ── Full-duplex voice (ElevenLabs) ───────────────────────────────────────────
# Required to enable the mic + spoken output. Stays server-side — the browser
# only ever receives short-lived tokens from /api/voice/*-token routes.
ELEVENLABS_API_KEY=sk_...

# The ElevenLabs voice used for Nova (client-side, so it needs NEXT_PUBLIC_).
# Defaults to a stock voice if unset.
# NEXT_PUBLIC_ELEVENLABS_VOICE_ID=uYXf8XasLslADfZ2MB4u

# ── Persistence ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# The mesh itself needs no database (in-process bus). What persists is each
# agent's store — transcripts + the inbox, where mesh state lives. Default is
# in-memory (gone on restart). Set "pglite" to persist via embedded Postgres
# (@electric-sql/pglite, pure WASM — no native bindings):
# VOICE_PERSIST=pglite
# Data directory for pglite mode (default: ./voice-agents-db):
# VOICE_DB_DIR=./voice-agents-db
# Clear everything: the "Clear data" button in the console, or `pnpm clear`
# (server stopped), or delete the data directory.

# ── Voice latency metrics ────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Every turn's timings (time-to-first-audio, STT latency, worker/relay latency,
# barge-ins) are appended to a local JSONL file for offline analysis.
# Default: ./voice-metrics.jsonl (relative to the app's working dir).
# VOICE_METRICS_FILE=./voice-metrics.jsonl
